/resource/Humphry_Greenwood\"}, {\"begin\": 275, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.9379650183803365e-12, \"text\": \"Louis Vuitton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\"}, {\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999874635251, \"rank\": 1.077261767794747e-08, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"silver and bronze medals\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/Stephanie Lecocq/Reuters Plans to pay prize money to athletes taking part in the Olympic Games this summer, risks \\\"polarizing\\\" the games, according to one sports historian.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"/Stephanie Lecocq/Reuters Plans\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 417}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 448}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"risks\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 523}, {\"ngram\": \"one sports historian\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 558}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Philip Barker, editor of the Journal of Olympic History, told CGTN Europe that the plans put the tradition of the 'gentleman amateur' among competitors at risk.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Philip Barker\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"editor\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 583}, {\"ngram\": \"the Journal\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic History\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"CGTN Europe\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"the plans\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'gentleman amateur\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 694}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 713}, {\"ngram\": \"risk\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics, the international athletics federation, says it will pay Olympic gold medal winners $50,000 at the Paris games in July.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.618325073856815e-14, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 3.3722209563724075e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the international athletics federation\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 779}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold medal winners\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletics governing body is putting aside a budget of $2.4m to reward winners across 48 events at the track and field programme.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The athletics\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"body\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"a budget\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"48 events\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"the track and field programme\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plans are also underway to pay silver and bronze medallists at the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999176907, \"rank\": 6.686390793308392e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Plans\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"silver and bronze medallists\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympics\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its President Sebastian Coe has admitted it is \\\"a pivotal moment\\\" for the Olympic movement but not at odds with the spirit of the games.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its President\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"a pivotal moment\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"odds\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The beneficiaries of growth are the sports and ultimately the athlete,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The beneficiaries\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"growth\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"the sports\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"ultimately the athlete\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think this sits firmly behind those principles and philosophies that they espouse as well.\\\"\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those principles\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"philosophies\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports historian Phillip Barker disagrees vehemently.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phillip_Barker_(film_director)\", \"score\": 0.9999963453745684, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phillip Barker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phillip_Barker_(film_director)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phillip_Barker_(film_director)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports historian\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told CGTN Europe: \\\"It's something that's going to polarize the Olympic world, not because the Olympics are amateur anymore, as they once were, but because the positioning of the Olympic Games is always that they are so much more than just a sporting event.\\\"\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CGTN Europe\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1480}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic world\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"the positioning\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"just a sporting event\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Describing a \\\"pecking order\\\" for Olympic sports, he predicted that the largest payments will be awarded to those taking part in track, gymnastics and aquatics events.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a \\\"pecking order\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sports\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest payments\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"aquatics events\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE Botswana offers to send Germany 20,000 elephants Genetic clues to left-handedness revealed European pasta market beats to Turkish durum Swedish pole vaulter Armand Duplantis calls the change \\\"a good thing\\\"/ Reuters Barker points out that this is not the first time financial incentives have been used at the games \\\"In fact, in 1993, in Stuttgart .. because Mercedes was sponsoring the championship and each winner got a car that was valued at around $28,000.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d However, describing regulations written when the modern games began in 1896, he adds the Olympic authorities \\\"set great store by being a gentleman amateur\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 There were people who were actually excluded from the Olympics because if they \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 played professionally as a cricketer, they could not compete as a footballer.\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 2688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1926, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9995693308217254, \"rank\": 0.00025571589936858693, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"score\": 0.8956224256904023, \"rank\": 0.11056434396905346, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\